[FILE:346:descriptions/desc.primary]
rs-tftpd is a pure Rust implementation of a Trivial File Transfer Protocol 
server daemon.

The server implements RFC 1350, The TFTP Protocol (Revision 2). It also 
supports the following RFC 2347 TFTP Option Extensions:

* RFC 2348 Blocksize Option
* RFC 2349 Timeout Interval Option
* RFC 2349 Transfer Size Option
* RFC 7440 Windowsize Option


[FILE:73:descriptions/desc.client]
This subpackage contains the tftpc TFTP client that comes with rs-tftpd.


